  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protect a village of 155 households from erosion</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">155 households live in Gatebe 2  village  in Rwanda, situated at the bottom of a hill . Due to heavy rain and unsustainable practices the community is hit by erosion and land degradation, threatening their subsistence farming livelihoods. Rwanda Development Organisation (RDO) plans to combat this situation by restoring the landscape by planting trees and improving drainage, and by sensitising the community about sustainable practices, including the distribution of 50 goats for organic manure.</narrative>
  </description>
